&lt;p&gt;Reporting to the Maintenance Superintendent, the Maintenance Supervisor will lead and direct their maintenance team to deliver safe, efficient, reliable and cost considered maintenance to our assets. They will be required to provide direction to the tradespeople and will be responsible for prioritizing and allocating their team to the workshop of both planned and unplanned maintenance work.&amp;nbsp; This includes maintaining a safe and efficient workplace, completing planned &amp;amp; unplanned maintenance events and ensuring that resources are allocated appropriately throughout the shift.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;KEY RESPONSIBILITIES&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Co-ordinate leading hands and maintenance crews to manage all mobile plant and equipment on site, during shift. Provide leadership and direction to all maintenance personnel including subcontractors. Ensure that all work undertaken is in accordance with direction from the Maintenance Superintendent and the Project SMP/EMP, OEM and SOPs.&amp;nbsp; Ensure that all equipment fleets achieve maximum availability for minimal cost.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure resource allocations of labor, tooling and equipment is optimized to meet both planned and unplanned maintenance work on each shift.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Constantly look to identify hazards and risks through regular inspections, audits, behavioral observations, JSEO’s as per HSE targets and review team member JSEO’s, where required, take corrective actions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead, coach and develop team members by setting clear expectations, monitoring performance and mentoring team members.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide clear performance expectations to personnel and subcontractors and reinforce correct behavior through recognition and encouragement as well as application of timely disciplinary procedures.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure down day activities are monitored for quality, effectiveness and compliance to Thiess standards&lt;/li&gt;
